25|$|The 112 and 114 are {{conventional}} layout monoplanes {{with the}} main wing set low and a mid-mounted <b>horizontal</b> <b>stabilizer.</b> This places the stabilizer outside the prop wash, and results in heavier handling at lower speeds.|$|E
25|$|The Scaled Composites Triumph was a twin-engine, {{business}} jet prototype {{designed and built}} for Beechcraft. The aircraft is a three lifting surface design, with both a small forward wing, and a small conventional <b>horizontal</b> <b>stabilizer</b> in a T-tail configuration.|$|E
25|$|The Scaled Composites Model 81 Catbird is a high-efficiency five-seat {{single-engine}} all-composite {{general aviation}} aircraft designed by Burt Rutan. It {{is unusual in}} that it incorporates both a small forward wing and a small conventional <b>horizontal</b> <b>stabilizer</b> on the tail.|$|E
