25|$|On 11 September 1991, Continental Express Flight 2574, an Embraer EMB 120 Brasilia, {{lost its}} <b>horizontal</b> <b>stabilizer</b> due to {{maintenance}} error while on approach to Houston Intercontinental Airport and crashed {{in a field}} near Eagle Lake, Texas, killing all 14 on board.|$|E
25|$|An {{investigation}} by the USAF determined that the crash was likely caused by an improper stabilizer trim setting. The investigation was unable to determine conclusively what had caused the <b>horizontal</b> <b>stabilizer</b> trim to be set improperly, but theorized that the most likely cause was an aircraft system malfunction.|$|E
